    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-08-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-08-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="495"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d495">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.512/855</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cunningham</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="60" xml:id="d495fn60">Copy transmitted to the Department by
                        the Chargé in China in his despatch No. 1608, August 13; received September
                        15.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-08-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 8, 1928</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I beg leave, adverting to your despatch No. 5550,
                    of July 10, 1928, and your radio message No. 251, of August 2, 1 p.m.,<note
                        n="61" xml:id="d495fn61">Neither printed.</note> both concerning the surtax
                    on imported coal imposed at Shanghai, to inform you that although this tax is
                    nominally a consumption tax, from the fact, as stated in your despatch, that it
                    is imposed on coal imported by an American firm, it appears to the Legation that
                    it partakes of the nature of a surtax on imports. For this reason you are
                    authorized, should such a course now appear to you advisable, to enter a protest
                    against its imposition.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">J. V. A. MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
